   <concept id="FAR_42_709_3" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">42.709-3</ph> Responsibilities.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> The
cognizant contracting officer is responsible for—</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Determining
whether the penalties in 
                           <xref href="42.709-2.dita#FAR_42_709_2"
                              base="FAR_42_709_1"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42.709-2</xref>(a) should
be assessed;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e24">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Determining
whether such penalties should be waived pursuant to 
                           <xref href="42.709-6.dita#FAR_42_709_6"
                              base="FAR_42_709_5"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42.709-6</xref>; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e32">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Referring
the matter to the appropriate criminal investigative organization
for review and for appropriate coordination of remedies, if there
is evidence that the contractor knowingly submitted unallowable
costs.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e37">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The contract
auditor, in the review and/or the determination of final indirect
cost proposals for contracts subject to this section, is responsible
for—</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e43">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Recommending
to the contracting officer which costs may be unallowable and subject
to the penalties in 
                           <xref href="42.709-2.dita#FAR_42_709_2"
                              base="FAR_42_709_1"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42.709-2</xref>(a);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e51">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Providing
rationale and supporting documentation for any recommendation; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2533e56">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Referring
the matter to the appropriate criminal investigative organization
for review and for appropriate coordination of remedies, if there
is evidence that the contractor knowingly submitted unallowable
costs.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
</dita>
